			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Meier Lenc, who lived in the Sokal Ghetto until its liquidation and then escaped to the “Aryan side”. He was captured
					by German police and later ran away from the grave he had been forced to dig for himself. He spent several months in Kuczków
					village and later joined a Soviet partisan unit.</p>
			</abstract>
